Greenback Athletics
August 10 at 3:43 PM ·

Greenbacks - Fall sports start next Monday! This year the Fall Sports Meetings will be for all parents grades 7-12.

The PHS/LMS Fall Sports Parents Meeting have been divided up by sport to help with Social Distancing and to provide opportunities to discuss KSHSAA Covid-19 mitigation protocols based upon the activity (inside, outside etc.). All meetings will start in the PHS Gym.

They will follow the format of previous year's meetings. After the Athletic Director's presentation, we will divide up by sport, social distance, and each coach will make their presentation. Please make this change on your calendar.

Fall 2020 PHS/LMS Parents Meetings
Thursday, August 13 @ 7:00 pm. Football and Cheer @ PHS Gym
Monday, August 17 @ 7:00 pm. Volleyball @ PHS Gym
Tuesday, August 18 @ 7:00 pm. Cross Country, Golf and Tennis @ PHS Gym

The PHS Booster Club Athletic Banquet scheduled for Monday, April 27 has been cancelled due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The Booster Club is planning an alternative way to honor Seniors and PHS Athletes. More information will follow in the future.

The Pratt High School All-Sports Program will be produced and a hard copy for Senior Parents will be in Senior Graduation Packets. Also, an On-line All Sports Program version will be available for the public later this spring.
The Senior Athletes of the Year, Senior Three-Sport Athletes and Scholarship WInners will still be announced at a to be determined date.

shared_text:
Greenback Athletics
March 12, 2019 at 9:00 AM ·

The Greenbacks are excited to announce Brent Hoelting as the new Greenback Head Football Coach. Coach Hoelting comes to Pratt from Lyndon High School. In his 5 years at Lyndon, he won 4 league titles and had 3 quarterfinal playoff appearances.

Prior to this, Coach Hoelting served as Defensive Coordinator at Chanute High School for 8 years. There his team advanced to the playoffs all 8 years with 3 quarterfinal appearances. Also, Chanute won 2 league titles, including the first one in over 70 years.

Coach Hoelting and his wife Andrea have three children Kamryn (6th grade), Kanon (4 years), and Lincoln (2 years)

You are invited to come meet Coach Hoelting tonight at 6 pm in the PHS Gym. Players, parents and community members are invited. The main west doors of Pratt High School will be open.

It's a busy week for the Pratt Greenbacks!
Thursday Pratt will host the league cross country meet. On Friday and Saturday, Pratt will host the girls state tennis meet. Friday at Zerger Field is senior night for football, cross country, girls golf and girls tennis. Friday is also "Pink Out" for breast cancer.

post_text:
It's the grind of the winter sports season. The Greenbacks are working hard this season. The boys and girls basketball teams earned 3rd place in their respective tournaments! The wrestling team placed 4th and 5th place in their last two tournaments. Good job Greenbacks!

A few upcoming events: This Friday is Winter Homecoming and the Booster Club Hog roast. It will be a great evening of food, basketball and Royalty! The second of only 2 home wrestling tournaments is Saturday February 11, as Pratt hosts the league tournament. Come out and support your Pratt Greenbacks!

Hey Greenback fans, take a break from the shopping, shake off the turkey coma, or sneak out of work for a while and come out to the send off for the PHS football team! Approximately 2:00 the bus will leave PHS and go down Main Street to 54 then up 61 highway.

GO BIG GREEN!!

shared_text:
Pratt High School Greenback Booster Club
October 9, 2016 at 10:38 AM ·

It has been a busy week for the Pratt Greenbacks! Homecoming, football games, regional tennis, golf, cross country and volleyball kept our student athletes, their coaches and families crazy busy. Oh, did I mention it was parent-teacher conferences this week too! The Greenback booster club would like to thank everyone for supporting our students. Whether you brought food for the regional tennis tournament we hosted or bought raffle tickets at the football game, or helped in so many other ways big or small, THANK YOU!

Thank you to Bill Rea for always taking great pictures. It is so nice of him to spend his time, his gas money, to share his talent and his photos, so friends and family can watch and cheer. If you see Bill thank him! This picture is a great one he took Friday. The football team definitely rocked it, but the cheerleaders, band and the student section were awesome too!

post_text: Don't miss the PHS Athletic Banquet scheduled for 6:30 pm next Monday, April 25th at the Municipal Building. This year's guest speaker is Mitch Holthus, voice of the Kansas City Chiefs and previously the voice of the Greenbacks. Meal is served first, followed by awards and speaker. The cost is $12 for the evening including the meal or $5 with no meal. Walk-ins welcome, but seating is limited.
